<!-- PB:B: heading --><h3 class="h4 m4" id="h2--ted-books">TED Books
</h3>

<!-- PB:B: copy --><div class='media'>
<div class='media__image' style='max-width: 30%'>
<figure class='Figure'>
<a href="http://geni.us/2mV1?track=topics" target="_blank"><img alt='TED Book: The Happiness Manifesto' class='Figure__image' src='//pb-assets.tedcdn.com/system/baubles/files/000/001/022/original/TEDBook_NicMarksspar_TEDBook.jpg?1401734299'>
</a></figure>
</div>
<div class='media__message'>
<div class='copy text-left'>
<h4 class="h7 m5">The Happiness Manifesto</h4>

<p><strong>by Nic Marks</strong><br>
We assume that economic prosperity leads to happiness -- and we're making ourselves miserable in the process. Nic Marks explores what would happen if we made happiness a national priority.<br>
<strong><a href="http://geni.us/2mV1?track=topics">Buy now</a></strong></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>



